<title>JAPAN: Japanese police hunt cyber-blackmailers.</title>
<headline>Japanese police hunt cyber-blackmailers.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Police are investigating threats by blackmailers to post unfavorable information about several Japanese companies on the Internet if those firms did not pay $5,000 each, Japanese media reported on Sunday.</p>
<p>The blackmailers sent typed letters to 20 companies in Tokyo and Osaka containing the threat, Kyodo news agency said.</p>
<p>The letters said information on the companies' cash flows had been obtained, alleging that it indicated the companies had received illegal funds, Kyodo said.</p>
<p>Police said there was no apparent pattern in the types of companies targeted, Kyodo said.</p>
<p>The group demanded the companies pay the $5,000 as &quot;relief money&quot; to an account at a bank in Bangkok, Kyodo quoted police sources as saying.</p>
